Compartment syndrome (ACS) is a clinical condition that occurs when there is an increase in pressure and/ or a decrease in the size of a muscle compartment resulting in reduced capillary blood flow and leading to cell death. If the pressure is not relieved within hours, irreversible damage to the tissues and nerves may result in contractures, paralysis, loss of sensation

